# Node.js + TypeScript Guidelines

## рџЏ—пёЏ Architecture вЂ” Layer Responsibilities

This project follows a strict layered architecture. Each layer has one job:

```
Request в†’ Router в†’ Controller в†’ Service в†’ Repository в†’ Prisma
```

| Layer | Responsibility | What it must NOT do |
|---|---|---|
| **Router** | Map HTTP verbs + paths to controller methods | Any logic |
| **Controller** | Parse request, call service, send response | Business logic, DB access |
| **Service** | Own all business logic | Import Prisma directly |
| **Repository** | All Prisma/DB access | Business logic |
| **Middleware** | Cross-cutting concerns (auth, logging, errors) | Business logic |

- Dependency injection always вЂ” pass repositories into services, don't instantiate inside
- This makes every layer unit-testable in isolation with a simple mock

```ts
// вњ… Good вЂ” injectable
class UserService {
  constructor(private readonly userRepository: UserRepository) {}
}

// вќЊ Bad вЂ” tightly coupled, untestable
class UserService {
  private repo = new UserRepository();
}
```

---

## рџ”· TypeScript вЂ” Strict Mode

`strict: true` is enabled. Respect it.

- **No `any`** вЂ” use `unknown` and narrow it, or define a proper type/interface
- **No type assertions (`as X`)** unless you can justify it in a comment
- All function parameters and return types must be explicitly typed
- Use `interface` for object shapes that may be extended; `type` for unions, intersections, utility types
- Prefer `readonly` on properties that should not be mutated

```ts
// вќЊ Bad
function processData(data: any) { ... }

// вњ… Good
function processData(data: unknown): ProcessedResult {
  if (!isValidData(data)) throw new ValidationError('Invalid data shape');
  // narrow and use
}
```

---

## вљ пёЏ Error Handling

- Use the error classes in `src/errors/AppError.ts` вЂ” `NotFoundError`, `ValidationError`, `ConflictError`
- Create new named subclasses for domain-specific errors as needed
- **Never throw generic `new Error('...')`** in services or repositories
- **Never swallow errors** вЂ” empty `catch` blocks are forbidden
- The global `errorHandler` middleware in `src/middleware/errorHandler.ts` handles HTTP responses вЂ” don't `res.status()` in catch blocks

```ts
// вќЊ Bad
if (!user) throw new Error('not found');

// вњ… Good
if (!user) throw new NotFoundError('User', id);
```

---

## вљЎ Async / Promises

- Always `async/await` вЂ” no `.then()/.catch()` chains
- Never fire-and-forget a Promise unless explicitly intentional with a comment
- Use `Promise.all` for concurrent independent async operations
- Every async function must have a typed return: `Promise<User>`, not just `Promise<any>`

---

## рџ§Є Testing Patterns

- **Unit tests**: test services and repositories in isolation вЂ” inject mocks via constructor
- **Integration tests**: use `supertest` against `createApp()` вЂ” never start the real server
- Test file lives next to the file it tests: `user.service.ts` в†’ `user.service.test.ts`
- Use `jest.fn()` for mocks вЂ” type them properly: `jest.fn() as jest.MockedFunction<typeof someFunction>`
- Never mock Prisma directly in service tests вЂ” mock the repository instead

```ts
// вњ… Correct test isolation
const mockUserRepository = {
  findById: jest.fn(),
  create: jest.fn(),
};
const userService = new UserService(mockUserRepository);
```

---

## рџ“Ѓ File Naming & Structure

```
src/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ config/         env.ts, prisma.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ errors/         AppError.ts (and subclasses)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ middleware/     errorHandler.ts, (auth.ts, etc.)
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ routes/         user.routes.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ controllers/    user.controller.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ services/       user.service.ts + user.service.test.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ repositories/   user.repository.ts + user.repository.test.ts
в””в”Ђв”Ђ __tests__/      integration tests (health.test.ts, etc.)
```

- `camelCase` for files, `PascalCase` for classes
- One class per file
- Named exports only вЂ” no default exports

---

## рџ”§ Config & Environment

- All env vars are validated and exported from `src/config/env.ts`
- Never access `process.env.X` outside of `src/config/env.ts`
- Never hardcode ports, URLs, secrets, or DB paths

---

## рџљ« Always Forbidden

- `any` type
- `console.log` in production code (use a logger or remove before committing)
- Empty `catch` blocks
- Default exports
- Accessing `process.env` outside `src/config/env.ts`
- Importing Prisma directly in a service
- Hardcoded secrets or URLs
- Commented-out code in commits
